[6] Iowa (Ida county): commercial turkeys
Date: Mon 12 Dec 2022
Source: Storm Lake Radio [edited]
https://stormlakeradio.com/news/2022/12/12/bird-flu-confirmed-in-ida-county-turkey-flock


According to agriculture officials, the affected site is a commercial turkey flock. This marks the 1st confirmed case of bird flu in an Ida Countyflock this year [2022].

There have now been 30 flocks infected with bird flu in Iowa this year, with 11 of them during the fall season. Since last Friday [9 Dec 2022], a total of approximately 240-thousand turkeys have been infected between turkey farms in Ida, Buena Vista, Sac, and Cherokee Counties. Around 16-million turkeys and chickens have had to be slaughtered in Iowa this year to limit the spread of the disease.

Avian influenza is a highly contagious viral disease affecting bird populations. The disease can travel in wild birds without those birds appearing to be sick, but is often fatal to domestic bird populations.

